    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-10-29</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-12-16T20:42:58Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Nuclear Energy Research Initiative Improvement Act of 2009 - Amends the Energy Policy Act of 2005 to direct the Secretary of Energy to: (1) conduct research to lower the cost of nuclear reactor systems; and (2) develop and publish on the Department of Energy (DOE) website a schedule outlining a five-year strategy to lower such cost effectively.</p> <p>Includes among research subjects: (1) modular and small-scale reactors; (2) balance-of-plant issues; (3) cost-efficient manufacturing and construction; (4) licensing issues; and (5) enhanced proliferation controls.</p> <p><br> </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>80</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2010-09-27</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to Senate without amendment</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2010-12-22T18:50:23Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary has been expanded because action occurred on the measure.)</b></p> <p>Nuclear Energy Research Initiative Improvement Act of 2009 - Amends the Energy Policy Act of 2005 to direct the Secretary of Energy to: (1) conduct research to lower the cost of nuclear reactor systems; and (2) develop and publish on the Department of Energy (DOE) website a schedule outlining a five-year strategy to lower such cost effectively, including public workshops to provide an opportunity for public comment.</p> <p>Includes among research subjects: (1) modular and small-scale reactors; (2) balance-of-plant issues; (3) cost-efficient manufacturing and construction; (4) licensing issues; and (5) enhanced proliferation controls.</p> <p>Authorizes appropriations for FY2011-FY2015.<br> <br> </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
